The paper deals with approximation algorithms for a geometric problem involving disks in the plane, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of local search and LP relaxation techniques also suggests connections to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The need for new combinatorial ideas and analysis techniques suggests connections to the sub-categories of graph theory (cs.GT) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
